---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/seo/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../config';

// NOTE (internal, not rendered): standard, conservative starting terms. Confirm
// the legal entity, governing law/venue, refund/SLA terms, and liability caps
// with counsel before relying on this.
const lastUpdated = 'July 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | GovHub"
  description="The terms that govern your use of GovHub's AI government proposal and compliance platform."
>
  <main class="container">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', url: '/' }, { name: 'Terms', url: '/terms/' }]} />

    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of GovHub's
        website and platform (the "Services"). By using the Services, you agree to
        these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Accounts</h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account
        credentials and for all activity under your account. Provide accurate
        information and keep it current.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree not to misuse the Services, including by attempting to disrupt
        them, access them without authorization, or use them for unlawful purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Your content</h2>
      <p>
        You retain ownership of the content you upload. You grant us the limited
        rights needed to operate the Services and to draft and review your
        proposals at your direction. We do not use your proposal content to train
        AI models.
      </p>

      <h2>4. AI-generated output</h2>
      <p>
        The Services generate draft content to assist you. You are responsible for
        reviewing, verifying, and finalizing all output before use or submission.
        GovHub does not guarantee award, compliance, or any particular outcome.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Fees</h2>
      <p>
        Paid plans are billed as described on the <a href="/pricing/">pricing
        page</a>. Unless stated otherwise, fees are non-refundable except as
        required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The Services, including software and content we provide, are owned by
        GovHub and protected by law. These Terms grant you a limited,
        non-exclusive right to use the Services.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        The Services are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind to the
        fullest extent permitted by law, including as to accuracy of AI-generated
        output.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, GovHub will not be liable for
        indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the
        Services.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        You may stop using the Services at any time. We may suspend or terminate
        access for violation of these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use after changes
        take effect constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Email
        <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main { padding: 1rem 1.5rem 3rem; }
  .prose { max-width: 44rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
  .updated { color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  h2 { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  p { color: var(--fg-muted); }
</style>
